Also the time comparisons (comparing one day to another or one month to another) is confusing.  By comparison, the eGauge monitoring system that came with my solar panel array is well designed, easy to read, fast and extremely useful.  I show the eGauge web page to friends and family to describe my energy usage and how my solar array works.  Everyone I have shown it to is extremely impressed by it.  I don't show the energy management system to anyone because, for the most part, I can't figure out what it is telling me and even then, it isn't very interesting."

Energy credit provides 12.9 cents per kWh, but charges for producing  1501-2500kWh is 15.1 cents per kWh and producing >2501kWh is 15.5 cents per kWh.
